# Foreman UI File Routing

- `dashboard.py` is the server/router/API entrypoint.
- `dashboard_ui_v3.py` owns the live SPA shell (`NEW_UI_HTML`) for `/chat`, `/projects`, `/inbox`, `/settings`.

## Required mapping before edits

- If task mentions chat bubbles, markdown rendering, RESULTS card, sidebar "Recent projects", or `/chat`, work in `dashboard_ui_v3.py` first.
- Only edit `dashboard.py` for route handling, backend/API behavior, auth/gating, or legacy templates not used by `/chat`.

## Verification checklist for UI tasks

- Confirm route mapping in `dashboard.py` points `/chat` to `NEW_UI_HTML`.
- Locate the exact rendering path in `dashboard_ui_v3.py` before changing code.
- If markdown is involved, check both:
  - bubble/history/stream rendering (`textContent` vs `innerHTML`)
  - sidebar project-title rendering (strip markdown for labels)

## Safety rule

- Do not assume `dashboard.py` template strings control the live `/chat` UI.
- If uncertain, verify with code search before editing.
